@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnImagePolishDemo — Phase 7.5 (design §"The proof surface"), route
    "/imagepolish", mount-registry key "BnImagePolishDemo". Authored in
    .razor.

    A NINTH page, same rationale as the fourth through eighth — and here the
    argument is at its sharpest, because the obvious alternative is
    extending "/image": BnImageDemo's two frame tables ARE the 6.3
    cross-platform parity contract, its section-offset arithmetic is
    golden-pinned, and its header says a new capability does not get to
    rewrite it. Appending sections would move BackSectionYDp and churn three
    surfaces of goldens for zero engine reason. So the new features get
    their own page, and Gate 1's bar includes "/image"'s goldens
    byte-identical — if a 6.3 number moves, the change is wrong.

    ── WHAT THIS PAGE PROVES ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Phase 7.5's one sentence: the three new features add ZERO new
    measurement states. Every case below is a 6.3 measurement path re-run
    WITH a new feature present, plus the one thing 6.3 could not have: an
    error the wire can talk about. The 6.3 discipline throughout — every
    case has a 20dp colored band under it, and THE BAND's y IS THE PROOF;
    declared-size sections first, so nothing above a no-move assertion can
    move it; the one reflowing section last-but-one; the back row last (the
    only font-measured leaf).

      [0] PLACEHOLDER-WHILE-LOADING — declared 200×120, PlaceholderColor,
          Src=/slow.png (held-until-released). While held: band L at
          y = 120, the placeholder paints (view-state pin: the drawable /
          image IS the placeholder). After releaseSlow: bytes paint,
          placeholder GONE (the state table's SUCCESS row), band L still at
          120 — the placeholder never bought or cost a single dp.
      [1] ERROR, SPACE KEPT — declared 200×120, PlaceholderColor,
          Src=/missing.png (404), OnError bound. After termination: band E
          IDENTICAL at y = 120 (the declared box held — because it was
          DECLARED, not because it failed), placeholder still painted (the
          ERROR row), OnError dispatched EXACTLY ONCE with payload
          …/missing.png (a counted wire dispatch, both shells), and the
          echo row below the band re-renders — a BnText inside a
          FIXED-HEIGHT row (the modal-switch-echo precedent), so the
          round-trip is a text assertion and the frame table stays static.
      [2] THE FOUR MODES — four images, one per ContentMode (wire order:
          contain / cover / stretch / center), same fixture (/fixed.png,
          64×48, 4:3), same declared 120×60 box (2:1 — an aspect the
          fixture disagrees with, so all four paint visibly differently
          against the shared backdrop color). THE assertion: FOUR IDENTICAL
          LAYOUT FRAMES — same x/w/h, y's in fixed 60+20 steps — under four
          different modes, bands pinned; per-node view-state pins
          (scaleType / contentMode property per mode, clipsToBounds true)
          carry the paint half (the 7.4 finding-4 lesson: assert the wiring
          where the paint cannot be synthesized).
      [3] PLACEHOLDER NEVER MEASURES, failing side — INTRINSIC (no size),
          PlaceholderColor, Src=/missing.png. Stays 0×0; band X at y = 0 IN
          ITS PARENT, forever. If a placeholder measured as ANYTHING, this
          band moves — decision 1's red line. (No OnError here — which is
          itself the attach-iff-HasDelegate pin on a device: this failure
          dispatches NOTHING.)
      [4] PLACEHOLDER NEVER MEASURES, loading side — INTRINSIC,
          PlaceholderColor, Src=/intrinsic.png. 0×0 before; natural 160×90
          after; band I moves 0 → Hi, ONCE — 6.3's reflow proof re-run with
          a placeholder present, pinning "one reflow, never two" against
          the exact feature 6.3 refused to ship for fear of it. LAST-BUT-ONE
          on purpose: its reflow propagates only into the back row.
      [5] the back row — nav parity, "← Back" → "/". LAST: a font-measured
          height never sits above a frame assertion.

    ── FIXTURES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    The existing in-process loopback servers (Android ImageFixtureServer.kt,
    iOS BnImageFixtureServer.swift): same origin :8099, same paths, same
    bind-exclusively / prove-the-bytes-are-ours rules. This page's sources
    REFERENCE BnImageDemo's constants — one origin, declared once. NEW to
    the servers (Gates 2/3): "/slow.png" — held until the suite calls the
    release hook, so the "while loading" rows are assertable states, not
    races. The demo app itself still reaches no server and shows failed
    images — correct, expected, documented (6.3's "TEST TARGETS, NOT THE
    APP" rule): what the APP shows on this page is the placeholder color in
    the three declared boxes (the ERROR row of the state table) — the first
    time a human can SEE a 7.5 feature without a test harness.

    ── THE SYNCHRONIZATION GATE — 6.3's, VERBATIM ───────────────────────────
    The AFTER assertions run only once EVERY request on the page has
    terminated (SIX: slow, error, 4× fixed — plus the two intrinsic ones =
    seven; count them ALL), counted via the loaders' terminal callbacks,
    never by polling a band, with the positive fixture-contract assertions
    up front. OnError JOINS the evidence (the counted dispatch is part of
    case [1]); it does not replace the gate — success still has no wire
    signal (no OnLoad — out of scope, named).

    Nav parity with every other page: "← Back" → INavigationManager → "/".
    Reachable by mount-name ("BnImagePolishDemo") and by route
    ("/imagepolish"); no button on BnDemo points here. Android's
    DEEP_LINK_COMPONENTS line is Gate 2's.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnColumn>
    @* [0] PLACEHOLDER-WHILE-LOADING — declared box, held source. Band L's
       y = 120 in BOTH states; the placeholder is paint, never size. *@
    <BnColumn Width="@SectionWidth" Align="FlexAlign.FlexStart">
        <BnImage Src="@SlowSrc" Width="@DeclaredWidth" Height="@DeclaredHeight"
                 PlaceholderColor="@PlaceholderHex" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderLoading" />
    </BnColumn>

    @* [1] ERROR, SPACE KEPT — declared box, 404 source, OnError bound. Band
       E's y = 120 forever (the box was DECLARED into its space); the echo
       row is FIXED-height so the dispatch round-trip re-renders text and
       moves nothing. *@
    <BnColumn Width="@SectionWidth" Align="FlexAlign.FlexStart">
        <BnImage Src="@ErrorSrc" Width="@DeclaredWidth" Height="@DeclaredHeight"
                 PlaceholderColor="@PlaceholderHex" OnError="OnImageError" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderError" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@EchoRowHeight">
            <BnText Text="@EchoText" />
        </BnView>
    </BnColumn>

    @* [2] THE FOUR MODES — one 64×48 fixture, four 120×60 boxes, four modes
       in wire order. Four IDENTICAL frames (mode is paint-only); the shared
       backdrop makes contain's bars / cover's crop / stretch's distortion /
       center's clipped natural size visible on a screenshot. *@
    <BnColumn Width="@SectionWidth" Align="FlexAlign.FlexStart">
        <BnImage Src="@ModeSrc" Width="@ModeBoxWidth" Height="@ModeBoxHeight"
                 ContentMode="ImageContentMode.Contain" BackgroundColor="@ModeBackdrop" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderModes" />
        <BnImage Src="@ModeSrc" Width="@ModeBoxWidth" Height="@ModeBoxHeight"
                 ContentMode="ImageContentMode.Cover" BackgroundColor="@ModeBackdrop" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderModes" />
        <BnImage Src="@ModeSrc" Width="@ModeBoxWidth" Height="@ModeBoxHeight"
                 ContentMode="ImageContentMode.Stretch" BackgroundColor="@ModeBackdrop" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderModes" />
        <BnImage Src="@ModeSrc" Width="@ModeBoxWidth" Height="@ModeBoxHeight"
                 ContentMode="ImageContentMode.Center" BackgroundColor="@ModeBackdrop" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderModes" />
    </BnColumn>

    @* [3] PLACEHOLDER NEVER MEASURES, failing side — intrinsic + placeholder
       + 404. Band X at y = 0 in its parent, forever: the decision-1 red
       line. No OnError — this failure dispatches nothing (attach iff
       HasDelegate, on a device). *@
    <BnColumn Width="@SectionWidth" Align="FlexAlign.FlexStart">
        <BnImage Src="@ErrorSrc" PlaceholderColor="@PlaceholderHex" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderIntrinsicFailing" />
    </BnColumn>

    @* [4] PLACEHOLDER NEVER MEASURES, loading side — THE REFLOW, re-run with
       a placeholder present. Band I: y 0 → Hi (90), exactly ONCE. *@
    <BnColumn Width="@SectionWidth" Align="FlexAlign.FlexStart">
        <BnImage Src="@IntrinsicSrc" PlaceholderColor="@PlaceholderHex" />
        <BnView Width="@SectionWidth" Height="@BandHeight" BackgroundColor="@BandUnderIntrinsicLoading" />
    </BnColumn>

    @* [5] nav parity — the page's only font-measured leaf, LAST. *@
    <BnRow Width="@SectionWidth">
        <BnButton Label="← Back" OnClick="GoBack" />
    </BnRow>
</BnColumn>

@code {
    // ── THE FIXTURES — BnImageDemo's, BY REFERENCE ────────────────────────────
    //
    // One origin, declared once (6.3's "a URL retyped in three places is a URL
    // that drifts in two", applied across pages): this page's sources alias the
    // /image constants wherever the path already exists, and declare only what
    // is new (the held source). The natural sizes both shells' fixture servers
    // are drift-pinned against live in BnImageDemo too — Hi
    // (IntrinsicNaturalHeightPx = 90) is exactly how far band I moves here.

    /// <summary>The in-process fixture origin — <see cref="BnImageDemo.FixtureOrigin"/>,
    /// verbatim (same server, same port, same bind-exclusively rules).</summary>
    internal const string FixtureOrigin = BnImageDemo.FixtureOrigin;

    /// <summary><b>[0]</b>'s source — NEW in 7.5: the fixture servers hold this
    /// response until the suite's release hook, so "while loading" is an
    /// assertable state, not a race. Natural size irrelevant (the box is
    /// declared); Gates 2/3 serve the 64×48 fixed fixture's bytes.</summary>
    internal const string SlowSrc = FixtureOrigin + "/slow.png";

    /// <summary><b>[1]</b>'s and <b>[3]</b>'s source — the 404 path, aliased from
    /// <see cref="BnImageDemo.FailingSrc"/>: a REAL failure, deterministic and
    /// offline, and ALSO the exact payload the <b>[1]</b> dispatch carries (the
    /// wire `src`, verbatim — decision 2).</summary>
    internal const string ErrorSrc = BnImageDemo.FailingSrc;

    /// <summary><b>[4]</b>'s source — <see cref="BnImageDemo.IntrinsicSrc"/>: the
    /// 160 × 90 fixture whose Hi IS the reflow.</summary>
    internal const string IntrinsicSrc = BnImageDemo.IntrinsicSrc;

    /// <summary><b>[2]</b>'s source, all four boxes — <see cref="BnImageDemo.FixedSrc"/>:
    /// the 64 × 48 fixture (4:3), deliberately disagreeing with the 2:1 mode box
    /// so all four modes paint visibly differently.</summary>
    internal const string ModeSrc = BnImageDemo.FixedSrc;

    // ── THE PAGE'S NUMBERS, AS CONSTANTS (the BnScrollDemo discipline) ────────
    //
    // BnImagePolishDemoTests asserts these off the WIRE (never transcribed), and
    // Gates 2/3 read them for the device assertions — one source of truth. The
    // section offsets are COMPUTED, so a changed band height reddens the golden
    // instead of desynchronising prose from wire.

    /// <summary>Every section is 300 wide (the /image discipline — and the
    /// AT_MOST constraint the intrinsic measure sees).</summary>
    internal const int SectionWidthDp = 300;

    /// <summary>Each case's band: 300 × 20. Its <b>y</b> is the whole proof
    /// surface of this page.</summary>
    internal const int BandHeightDp = 20;

    /// <summary>The declared box of cases <b>[0]</b> and <b>[1]</b> — /image case
    /// [0]'s numbers, on purpose: the box the 6.3 contract already proves is
    /// never measured.</summary>
    internal const int DeclaredWidthDp = 200;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="DeclaredWidthDp"/>
    internal const int DeclaredHeightDp = 120;

    /// <summary><b>[1]</b>'s echo row: FIXED height, so the error round-trip
    /// re-renders TEXT inside a box that cannot move (the modal-switch-echo
    /// precedent) and the frame table stays static.</summary>
    internal const int EchoRowHeightDp = 24;

    /// <summary><b>[2]</b>'s box, all four modes: 120 × 60 — 2:1 against the
    /// fixture's 4:3, so fit/fill/stretch/center are four different paints in
    /// FOUR IDENTICAL FRAMES.</summary>
    internal const int ModeBoxWidthDp = 120;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="ModeBoxWidthDp"/>
    internal const int ModeBoxHeightDp = 60;

    /// <summary>The placeholder color every placeholder case carries — one
    /// value, so the view-state pin ("the drawable IS the placeholder") is the
    /// same assertion on every node.</summary>
    internal const string PlaceholderHex = "#FFCA28";

    // ── THE ARITHMETIC (asserted by the golden, read by Gates 2/3) ────────────

    /// <summary><b>[0]</b> hugs 120 + 20 = 140. Nothing measured inside.</summary>
    internal const int LoadingSectionHeightDp = DeclaredHeightDp + BandHeightDp;

    /// <summary><b>[1]</b> starts where <b>[0]</b> ends — fixed in BOTH states
    /// (everything above is declared).</summary>
    internal const int ErrorSectionYDp = LoadingSectionHeightDp;

    /// <summary><b>[1]</b> hugs 120 + 20 + 24 = 164 — and holds it through the
    /// error AND the echo re-render.</summary>
    internal const int ErrorSectionHeightDp = DeclaredHeightDp + BandHeightDp + EchoRowHeightDp;

    /// <summary><b>[2]</b>'s y: 140 + 164 = 304.</summary>
    internal const int QuartetSectionYDp = ErrorSectionYDp + ErrorSectionHeightDp;

    /// <summary>The quartet's rhythm: each mode row is box + band = 60 + 20 =
    /// 80 — "y's in fixed 60+20 steps" (the design's words).</summary>
    internal const int ModeStepDp = ModeBoxHeightDp + BandHeightDp;

    /// <summary><b>[2]</b> hugs 4 × 80 = 320.</summary>
    internal const int QuartetSectionHeightDp = 4 * ModeStepDp;

    /// <summary><b>[3]</b>'s y: 304 + 320 = 624 — and its image is 0 × 0 in both
    /// states, so the section is band-only: 20 high, forever.</summary>
    internal const int IntrinsicFailingSectionYDp = QuartetSectionYDp + QuartetSectionHeightDp;

    /// <summary><b>[4]</b>'s y: 624 + 20 = 644. Fixed in both states — the
    /// reflow is INSIDE this section, and propagates only downward.</summary>
    internal const int IntrinsicLoadingSectionYDp = IntrinsicFailingSectionYDp + BandHeightDp;

    /// <summary>The back row's y BEFORE the bytes: 644 + 20 = 664; AFTER, this
    /// + Hi (<see cref="BnImageDemo.IntrinsicNaturalHeightPx"/> = 90) = 754 —
    /// <b>[4]</b>'s reflow, the page's ONLY moving number.</summary>
    internal const int BackSectionYDp = IntrinsicLoadingSectionYDp + BandHeightDp;

    /// <summary>The echo line, formatted ONCE for every surface (the
    /// BnFormDemo/BnModalDemo pattern), invariant: the dispatch count and the
    /// failed src the handler received. Mount state: <c>"err:0"</c>. After
    /// case [1] terminates: <c>"err:1 " + ErrorSrc</c> — "exactly once" is a
    /// TEXT assertion, on every surface.</summary>
    internal static string Echo(int count, string? src) => src is null
        ? string.Create(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, $"err:{count}")
        : string.Create(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, $"err:{count} {src}");

    // The band colours: distinct per case (Gates 2/3 read a reflow off a
    // SCREENSHOT as well as off a number). The quartet shares ONE band colour —
    // its four bands are distinguished by the 80dp rhythm, and what differs
    // per row is the PAINT above, against the shared backdrop.
    private const string BandUnderLoading = "#42A5F5";          // blue
    private const string BandUnderError = "#EF5350";            // red
    private const string BandUnderModes = "#AB47BC";            // purple ×4
    private const string BandUnderIntrinsicFailing = "#FF7043"; // deep orange
    private const string BandUnderIntrinsicLoading = "#66BB6A"; // green

    /// <summary>The mode boxes' backdrop — opaque, so contain's letterbox bars
    /// (which show BACKGROUND, never the placeholder — the state table's
    /// SUCCESS row) and center's surround are visible paint on a screenshot.</summary>
    private const string ModeBackdrop = "#263238";

    private int _errorCount;
    private string? _lastErrorSrc;

    private string EchoText => Echo(_errorCount, _lastErrorSrc);

    /// <summary>Case [1]'s handler — counts and records, so BOTH halves of the
    /// dispatch contract ("exactly once", "the payload is the wire src,
    /// verbatim") are one re-rendered string.</summary>
    private void OnImageError(BnImageErrorEventArgs e)
    {
        _errorCount++;
        _lastErrorSrc = e.Src;
    }

    private static readonly string SectionWidth =
        SectionWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string BandHeight =
        BandHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string DeclaredWidth =
        DeclaredWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string DeclaredHeight =
        DeclaredHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string EchoRowHeight =
        EchoRowHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string ModeBoxWidth =
        ModeBoxWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string ModeBoxHeight =
        ModeBoxHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    private Task GoBack() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/").AsTask();
}
